  "body": "As an Besu Operator, \r\nI want to upgrade Besu from 21.10.5 to 22.1.0 \r\nso that I can have my node updated. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* The node is sucessfully update\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Configure an IBFT network with static nodes with DNS Entries\r\n2. Enabled the features for DNS Xdns-enabled=true and Xdns-update-enabled=true and discovery disabled\r\n3. Boot up the network with Besu 22.1.0 version\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** \r\nThe network boot up and start producing blocks\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** \r\nThe peers are systematically rejected by each peer\r\n\r\n**Frequency:**\r\nBoot up of the node \r\n\r\n### Versions\r\n* Software version: [`besu --version`]  22.1.0\r\n* Docker Version: [`docker version`] 22.1.0\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nThe problem is caused by the function used to compare the node to beeing permissioned against the static-nodes. The internal  of this function destinationEnode.toURIWithoutDiscoveryPort(), is ignoring the logic of the DNS logic.\r\n\r\n",
